# Editor Conventions (SwingEditor)

The editor (`SwingEditor`) reuses the runtime `Database`/V2 persistence layer.
Static data lives in left-tab panels; save games/guild in a second top tab.

## Data-type panel pattern

A new data-type tab extends `EditorPanel` (implements `IEditorPanel`): a name list
+ detail form.

```java
public class MyThingPanel extends EditorPanel {
    public MyThingPanel() { super(SwingEditor.Tab.MY_THING); } // register a dirty bit
    public Container getEditControls() { /* build form */ }
    public void loadData() { /* names from Database.getInstance().getMyThings() */ }
    public void refresh(String name) { /* cache -> UI */ }
    public DataObject commit(String name) { /* UI -> in-memory cache */ }
}
```

- Any edit must flag dirty: `SwingEditor.instance.setDirty(dirtyFlag)`.
- Switching list selection auto-commits the previous item.
- Sub-widgets receive a `dirtyFlag` int and propagate `setDirty` upward.

## Save model (two-phase)

1. **Commit**: UI -> in-memory `Database` cache (`commit()` / `commitAll()`).
2. **Apply / Apply All**: flush dirty categories to disk via
   `Database.getInstance().saveXxx(...)` -> `V2Saver`.

Zones are special: `MapEditor` / `ZonePanel` persist immediately via
`Saver.saveZone()`, not via the bulk apply flow.

## Notes

- No undo stack; validation is ad-hoc. Be careful with destructive operations.
- `MapEditor` edits both the Crusader geometry and game-logic tiles via selection
  proxies (`SingleTileProxy`/`MultipleTileProxy`, etc.) - keep both layers in sync.
